Central meeting of Koreans in Japan held to celebrate Kim Jong Il's birthday
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tokyo, February 15 (KNS-KCNA) -- A central meeting of Koreans in Japan was held at the Korean Hall of Culture in Tokyo on Feb. 15 to celebrate the 57th birthday of General Secretary Kim Jong Il.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Ho Jong Man, chief vice-chairman of the central standing committee of the General Association of Korean Residents In Japan (Chongryon), made  a report at the meeting.
   He said that the last 5-year-long revolutionary history of the respected Marshal Kim Jong Il after the death of the great leader Generalissimo Kim Il Sung has fully  demonstrated the Marshal's noble trait and distinguished feats as a great statesman, outstanding military strategist and a benevolent father of the people. The Marshal is the destiny of the Korean nation and the symbol of the victory and glory of the socialist cause, the cause of Juche, the reporter noted.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He further said:   Only victory and glory are in store for Chongryon and Koreans in Japan who are advancing with concerted efforts under the wise leadership of the Marshal.   He called for vigorously advancing with the firm conviction of victory under the Marshal's leadership.   A congratulatory message of the Chongryon central standing committee to the Marshal was read out at the meeting.
   That day a banquet was given to celebrate his 57th birthday.

Reception for overseas Koreans
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 17 (KCNA) -- A reception was given here on Tuesday in honor of overseas Koreans in celebration of the 57th birthday of General Secretary Kim Jong Il.
   Speeches were made at the reception.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Head of the congratulatory group of Koreans in Japan So Man Sul, first vice-chairman of the central standing committee of the General Association of Korean Residents In Japan (Chongryon), said that to highly praise the respected Marshal Kim Jong Il as the sun of the 21st century is a trend of history and the unanimous aspiration of humankind.
   He further noted: Only when we trust and follow the Marshal can we overcome any ordeals and a bright way will open ahead of us. This is the patriotic faith cherished by overseas Koreans in Japan together with the people in the homeland.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Head of the congratulatory group of the confederation of Korean nationals in China Choe Chong San said that Kim Jong Il, giving on-site guidance to People's Army units, has grown it into a matchless army, made the whole country permeated with the spirit of Kanggye and lit the torch of advance at the Songjin Steel Complex. And he set this year as a year of a great turning-point for building a powerful nation and is wisely leading the struggle for its materialization.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Jon Sun Yong, head of the congratulatory group of the Federation of Koreans In Canada, stressed that overseas Koreans will vigorously take the road of patriotism for the country's reunification, prosperity and development, deeply cherishing the pride of Kim Il Sung's nation in having Marshal Kim Jong Il.
   Head of the congratulatory group of the International United Confederation of Koreans Jo Yun Hae said that they, together with the people in the homeland, would make a tangible contribution to reunifying the country and building a powerful socialist nation, bearing deep in mind the absolute worship and loyalty to General Secretary Kim Jong Il. 
   An art performance was given by artistes in Pyongyang at the reception.

Foreign party delegations arrive 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 17 (KCNA) -- The Central Committee of the Worker's Party of Korea gave a banquet at the Mokran House on Tuesday evening to mark the birthday of General Secretary Kim Jong Il.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present on invitation were visiting delegations of the Party for Peace and Unity of Russia, the Bangladesh People's League, the Unified Communist Party of Italy and the Syrian Arab Socialist Baath Party, the general secretary of the Communist Party of Ireland (Marxism-Leninism), the chairman of the People's Front of Workers, Peasants and Students of Peru, the delegate of the Romanian Socialist Party, the delegate of the Funcinpec Party of Cambodia, the delegate of the October 8 Revolutionary Movement of Brazil, the director general of the International Institute of the Juche Idea and his associates, the delegation of Japanese Teachers for Japan-DPRK Friendship, the chairman of the Shigoku Juche Idea Study Society of Japan, the delegation of the Liberal Women's Intellectual Fund of Mongolia, delegations to the 3rd Kimjongilia show and other foreign guests.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Choe Thae Bok, alternate politburo member and secretary of the WPK Central Committee, addressed the banquet.
   He said one of the most brilliant exploits performed by the respected Kim Jong Il in the course of leading the Korean Revolution is that he strengthened the Worker's Party of Korea into a Juche-type revolutionary party and invincible steel-like party that does not waver in any storm and stress.
   Kim Jong Il's Juche-oriented idea and theory represent the guiding principle of the WPK. His mode of politics is that of the WPK  and the wholehearted unity around him constitutes that of the WPK, Choe Thae Bok said, adding that the Worker's Party and people of Korea would smash the imperialists' anti-DPRK, anti-socialist moves and build a powerful socialist state in Korea under his wise leadership.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The secretary of the WPK Central Committee said national reunification is the supreme desire of the Korean people and the supreme task of the Korean nation. The historic cause of national reunification will certainly be achieved with concerted efforts of the nation through the implementation of the 3 major charters of reunification and the five-point policy of great national unity under the leadership of Kim Jong Il, the secretary pointed out.
   He said the WPK would work hard as ever to strengthen friendship and unity with all progressives of the world who advocate anti-imperialism, independence and socialism and to build a new world, independent and peaceful.
   The floor was also taken by Sazhi Umalatova, head of the delegation of the Party for Peace and Unity of Russia  Garib Newaz, head of the delegation of the Bangladesh People's League and Eduardo Fernandez, delegate of the October 8 Revolutionary Movement of Brazil.
   The banquet participants enjoyed a performance given by artistes in Pyongyang.
